_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"4656","uuid":"0770224e-8d99-450a-89d7-8be99e6e780b","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CBC71CAB43C4B27A6895D1D5434AF9B873258B9F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that the \"/var/log/\"messages file is owned by root.' is not present or not in use on this the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281036","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281036","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281036","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-281036r1165463_rule","rule_id":"SV-281036","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400095","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that the \"/var/log/messages\" file is group-owned by \"root\".","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the group owner of the \"/var/log/messages\" file is set to \"root\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root /var/log/messages","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the \"/var/log/messages\" file is group-owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c \"%G %n\" /var/log/messages\nroot /var/log/messages\n\nIf \"/var/log/messages\" does not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify the RHEL 10 system or platform. Additionally, personally identifiable information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"5859","uuid":"c47831ec-7118-4df5-ac45-5cb282214b4f","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A3F878E980953AB492CD7D460E92D2197325985D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that the \"/var/log/messages\" file is group-owned by \"root\".' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281037","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281037","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281037","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281037r1165466_rule","rule_id":"SV-281037","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400100","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that system commands are owned by \"root\".","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the system commands are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[FILE]\" with any system command file not owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chown root [FILE]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the system commands contained in the following directories are owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /bin /sbin /usr/bin /usr/sbin /usr/libexec /usr/local/bin /usr/local/sbin ! -user root -exec stat -L -c \"%U %n\" {} \\;\n\nIf any system commands are found to not be owned by root, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"2406","uuid":"3fe2198f-642d-4504-ba6b-8bfebe89ab7b","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 87F0094E480B3D6A07E6018932117FB871E73DD7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that system commands are owned by \"root\".' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281038","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281038","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281038","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281038r1184683_rule","rule_id":"SV-281038","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400105","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that system commands are group-owned by root or a system account.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the system commands are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[FILE]\" with any system command file not group-owned by \"root\" or a required system account.\n\n$ sudo chgrp root [FILE]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the system commands contained in the following directories are group-owned by \"root\", or a required system account, with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /bin /sbin /usr/bin /usr/sbin /usr/libexec /usr/local/bin /usr/local/sbin ! -group root -exec stat -L -c \"%G %n\" {} \\;\n\nIf any system commands are returned and are not group-owned by \"root\" or a required system account, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"8157","uuid":"d5f86db8-cf25-4309-a03f-696b6cce5a09","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 26D52CD1D9F5D429BE7D944C0EDBF2D7B51A62FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that system commands are group-owned by root or a system account.' is not present or not in use on this the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281039","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281039","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281039","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281039r1165472_rule","rule_id":"SV-281039","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400110","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that library files are owned by \"root\".","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the systemwide shared library files (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib, and /usr/lib64) are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[FILE]\" with any library file not owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chown root [FILE]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the systemwide shared library files are owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 ! -user root ! -type d -exec stat -L -c \"%U %n\" {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library file is not owned by root, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"7146","uuid":"ea98749f-9912-461f-ba90-3409ba38ee06","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 906B64F6D9E898538CF1B7C9B9D8585F6A966D1D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that library files are owned by \"root\".' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281040","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281040","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281040","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281040r1184734_rule","rule_id":"SV-281040","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400115","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that library files are group-owned by \"root\" or a system account.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the systemwide shared library files (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib, and /usr/lib64) are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[FILE]\" with any library file not group-owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chgrp root [FILE]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the systemwide shared library files are group-owned by \"root\"  or a system account with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 ! -group root ! -type d -exec stat -L -c \"%G %n\" {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library file is returned and is not group-owned by \"root\" or a required system account, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"5121","uuid":"f43c5b06-dada-4250-90af-33768aa760ce","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 911E62023A3B68C06E0DCC76641FBA3ECF160B5D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that library files are group-owned by \"root\" or a system account.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281041","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281041","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281041","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281041r1165478_rule","rule_id":"SV-281041","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400120","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that library directories are owned by \"root\".","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the systemwide shared library directories (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib, and /usr/lib64) are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[DIRECTORY]\" with any library directory not owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chown root [DIRECTORY]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the systemwide shared library directories are owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 ! -user root -type d -exec stat -c \"%U %n\" {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library directory is not owned by \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"7092","uuid":"e158d2d8-3ef4-46a8-a6b1-f89b7de4ee5c","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2FE66D195905354B9AC7184905406B56F56D97AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that library directories are owned by \"root\".' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281042","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281042","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281042","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281042r1184676_rule","rule_id":"SV-281042","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400125","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that library directories are group-owned by \"root\" or a system account.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the systemwide shared library directories (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib and /usr/lib64) are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[DIRECTORY]\" with any library directory not group-owned by \"root\".\n\n$ sudo chgrp root [DIRECTORY]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the systemwide shared library directories are group-owned by \"root\" or a system account with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 ! -group root -type d -exec stat -c \"%G %n\" {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library directory is returned and is not group-owned by \"root\" or a required system account, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"1559","uuid":"09957b8a-09ae-4f9e-8be7-da85b2a386cb","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9FBB78F250DD8FA68117657A92220371787A2502\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that library directories are group-owned by \"root\" or a system account.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281043","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281043","title":"SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281043","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000445-GPOS-00199","rule_id_src":"SV-281043r1184617_rule","rule_id":"SV-281043","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400130","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that cron configuration file directories are owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that cron configuration file directories are owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root [cron config file]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 ownership of all cron configuration files with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c \"%U %n\" /etc/cron*\nroot /etc/cron.d\nroot /etc/cron.daily\nroot /etc/cron.deny\nroot /etc/cron.hourly\nroot /etc/cron.monthly\nroot /etc/crontab\nroot /etc/cron.weekly\n\nIf any crontab is not owned by root, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Service configuration files enable or disable features of their respective services, which if configured incorrectly could lead to insecure and vulnerable configurations. Therefore, service configuration files must be owned by the correct group to prevent unauthorized changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002696"],"reference_identifier":"4868","uuid":"41fe60d8-afed-4da8-9f1a-2068832dd378","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ADF3FE9216364CD0E8C11AA81D0502F17002A3B2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that cron configuration file directories are owned by root.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281044","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281044","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281044","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281044r1184618_rule","rule_id":"SV-281044","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400135","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that cron configuration files directories are group-owned by root.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that any cron configuration file directories are group-owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root [cron config file]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 group ownership of all cron configuration files with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c \"%G %n\" /etc/cron*\nroot /etc/cron.d\nroot /etc/cron.daily\nroot /etc/cron.deny\nroot /etc/cron.hourly\nroot /etc/cron.monthly\nroot /etc/crontab\nroot /etc/cron.weekly\n\nIf any crontab is not group-owned by \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Service configuration files enable or disable features of their respective services, which if configured incorrectly can lead to insecure and vulnerable configurations. Therefore, service configuration files should be owned by the correct group to prevent unauthorized changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2162","uuid":"9497ade6-935d-4690-a395-64fd6cb723f7","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EDEF53DC5D3C082A7652A7FEF73DB90C28E41CAB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that cron configuration files directories are group-owned by root.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281045","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281045","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281045","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-281045r1165490_rule","rule_id":"SV-281045","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400140","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that world-writable directories are owned by root, sys, bin, or an application user.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 public directories to be owned by root or a system account to prevent unauthorized and unintended information transferred via shared system resources.\n\nUse the following command template to set ownership of public directories to root or a system account:\n\n$ sudo chown [root or system account] [Public Directory]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 world-writable directories are owned by root, a system account, or an application account with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find / -xdev -type d -perm -0002 -uid +999 -exec stat -c \"%U, %u, %A, %n\" {} \\; 2>/dev/null\n\nIf output indicates that world-writable directories are owned by any account other than root or an approved system account, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a world-writable directory is not owned by root, sys, bin, or an application user identifier (UID), unauthorized users may be able to modify files created by others.\n\nThe only authorized public directories are temporary directories supplied with the system or those designed to be temporary file repositories. The setting is normally reserved for directories used by the system and by users for temporary file storage, (e.g., /tmp), and for directories requiring global read/write access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5252","uuid":"50b64ae6-13aa-44ed-8886-d3e2a23a9e8e","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 800BB1BBBE00908025A74878A494D26BD472E950\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that world-writable directories are owned by root, sys, bin, or an application user.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281046","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281046","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281046","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281046r1165493_rule","rule_id":"SV-281046","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400145","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that all system device files are correctly labeled to prevent unauthorized modification.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that all system device files are correctly labeled to prevent unauthorized modification.\n\nRestore the SELinux policy for the affected device file from the system policy database using the following command:\n\n$ sudo restorecon -v <device_path>\n\nSubstitute \"<device_path>\" with the path to the affected device file (from the output of the previous commands). An example device file path would be \"/dev/ttyUSB0\". \n\nIf the output of the above command does not indicate that the device was relabeled to a more specific SELinux type label, the SELinux policy of the system must be updated with more specific policy for the device class specified. \n\nIf a package was used to install support for a device class, that package could be reinstalled using the following command:\n\n$ sudo dnf reinstall <package_name>\n\nIf a package was not used to install the SELinux policy for a given device class, it must be generated manually and provide specific type labels.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that all system device files are correctly labeled to prevent unauthorized modification.\n\nList all device files on the system that are incorrectly labeled with the following commands:\n\nNote: Device files are normally found under \"/dev\", but applications may place device files in other directories and may necessitate a search of the entire system.\n\n$ sudo find /dev -context *:device_t:* \\( -type c -o -type b \\) -printf \"%p %Z\\n\"\n\n$ sudo find /dev -context *:unlabeled_t:* \\( -type c -o -type b \\) -printf \"%p %Z\\n\"\n\nNote: There are device files, such as \"/dev/vmci\", that are used when the operating system is a host virtual machine. They will not be owned by a user on the system and require the \"device_t\" label to operate. These device files are not a finding.\n\nIf there is output from either of these commands, other than already noted, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If an unauthorized or modified device is allowed to exist on the system, the system may perform unintended or unauthorized operations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6139","uuid":"ed121fc8-7217-437d-9d8b-cd0eadfec091","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FA9BE78CBB0BFA97C0B64F8224DDAA80306CAF47\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that all system device files are correctly labeled to prevent unauthorized modification.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281047","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281047","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281047","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281047r1184647_rule","rule_id":"SV-281047","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400150","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that the Secure Shell (SSH) server configuration file is group-owned by \"root\".","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file and the contents of \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" are group-owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file and the contents of \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" are group-owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d -exec stat -c \"%G %n\" {} \\;\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-cloud-init.conf\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-redhat.conf\n\nIf the \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file or \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" or any files in the \"sshd_config.d\" directory do not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Service configuration files enable or disable features of their respective services, which if configured incorrectly can lead to insecure and vulnerable configurations. Therefore, service configuration files must be owned by the correct group to prevent unauthorized changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"4858","uuid":"3dcf8354-5240-4997-a71b-64c018568793","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1230F2E8177E901F2352DE1D55EE5A1C426B8179\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that the Secure Shell (SSH) server configuration file is group-owned by \"root\".' is not present or not in use on this the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281048","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281048","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281048","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281048r1184648_rule","rule_id":"SV-281048","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400155","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured so that the Secure Shell (SSH) server configuration file is owned by \"root\".","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file and the contents of \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" are owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown -R root /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file and the contents of \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" are owned by root with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d -exec stat -c \"%U %n\" {} \\;\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-cloud-init.conf\nroot /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-redhat.conf\n\nIf the \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" file or \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d\" or any files in the \"sshd_config.d\" directory do not have an owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Service configuration files enable or disable features of their respective services, which if configured incorrectly can lead to insecure and vulnerable configurations. Therefore, service configuration files must be owned by the correct group to prevent unauthorized changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9176","uuid":"2b911b35-5462-49d5-a2d1-7014fb1436a8","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 53F8EA94F1212941558E9A1CA4F9B2D2EA77F921\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'RHEL 10 must be configured so that the Secure Shell (SSH) server configuration file is owned by \"root\".' is not present or not in use on this the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281049","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281049","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281049","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281049r1197223_rule","rule_id":"SV-281049","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400160","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must ensure that all local interactive user home directories are group-owned by the home directory owner's primary group.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 interactive users' home directories to be group-owned by the user's primary GID.\n\nChange the group owner of a local interactive user's home directory to the group found in \"/etc/passwd\". To change the group owner of a local interactive user's home directory, use the following command:\n\nNote: The example will be for the user \"disauser\", who has a home directory of \"/home/disauser\" and has a primary group of users.\n\n$ sudo chgrp users /home/disauser","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 interactive users' home directories are group-owned by the user's primary GID with the following command:\n\nNote: This may miss local interactive users that have been assigned a privileged user identifier (UID). Evidence of interactive use may be obtained from several log files containing system login information. The returned directory \"/home/disauser\" is used as an example.\n\n$ sudo ls -ld $(awk -F: '($3>=1000)&&($7 !~ /nologin/){print $6}' /etc/passwd)\ndrwxr-x--- 2 disauser admin 4096 Jun 5 12:41 disauser\n\nCheck the user's primary group with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep $(grep disauser /etc/passwd | awk -F: '{print $4}') /etc/group\nadmin:x:250:disauser,doduser,nsauser\n\nIf the user home directory referenced in \"/etc/passwd\" is not group-owned by that user's primary GID, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the group identifier (GID) of a local interactive user's home directory is not the same as the primary GID of the user, this would allow unauthorized access to the user's files. Users who share the same group may not be able to access files that they legitimately should be able to access.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048, SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"9656","uuid":"36f9f447-f610-451d-860e-6641b6988bc1","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 40A7383895C27D3EE7191D34B7D1D8ADC4E585C1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must ensure that all local interactive user home directories are group-owned by the home directory owner's primary group.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281050","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281050","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281050","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-281050r1184685_rule","rule_id":"SV-281050","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400165","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce group ownership of audit logs by \"root\" or by a restricted logging group to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 to prevent unauthorized read access by ensuring that audit logs are group-owned by root or by a restricted logging group.\n\nChange the group of the directory of \"/var/log/audit\" to be owned by a correct group.\n\nIdentify the group that is configured to own audit logs:\n\n$ sudo grep -P '^[ ]*log_group[ ]+=.*$' /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nChange the ownership to that group:\n\n$ sudo chgrp ${GROUP} /var/log/audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 audit logs are group-owned by \"root\" or a restricted logging group.\n\nDetermine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nUsing the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log is group-owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%G %n\" /var/log/audit/audit.log\nroot /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nIf the audit log is not group-owned by \"root\" or the configured alternative logging group, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"5439","uuid":"aa45a05a-b18e-415f-b2f1-9d9286997c17","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C44868194CBA906D08D91B77A0D700B4B420BFA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce group ownership of audit logs by \"root\" or by a restricted logging group to prevent unauthorized read access.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281051","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281051","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281051","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-281051r1165508_rule","rule_id":"SV-281051","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400170","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce \"root\" ownership of the audit log directory to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 to prevent unauthorized read access by ensuring the audit log directory is \"root\" owned with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /var/log/audit","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 audit logs directory is owned by \"root\".\n\nDetermine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nUsing the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log directory is owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c '%U %n' /var/log/audit\nroot /var/log/audit\n\nIf the audit log directory is not owned by \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"6047","uuid":"0bd1e9d3-8f57-4696-b3ce-ff5557520a95","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 55FC388BF75EC72D460C9B45A1EE085B87CFE007\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce \"root\" ownership of the audit log directory to prevent unauthorized read access.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281052","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281052","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281052","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-281052r1165511_rule","rule_id":"SV-281052","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400175","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce \"root\" ownership of audit logs to prevent unauthorized access.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 to enforce \"root\" ownership of audit logs to prevent unauthorized access with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root [audit_log_file]\n\nReplace \"[audit_log_file]\" with the correct audit log path. By default this location is \"/var/log/audit/audit.log\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 enforces \"root\" ownership of audit logs to prevent unauthorized access.\n\nDetermine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep \"^log_file\" /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nUsing the location of the audit log file, determine if the audit log files are owned by \"root\" using the following command:\n\n$ sudo ls -la /var/log/audit/audit.log\nrw-------. 2 root root 237923 Jun 11 11:56 /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nIf the audit logs are not owned by \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"1729","uuid":"dadba15a-7556-41e7-9466-0d0841e0e284","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FBA33A0F72DDE5EB97B8155121DDD37D46EA2ED7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce \"root\" ownership of audit logs to prevent unauthorized access.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281053","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281053","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281053","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-281053r1165514_rule","rule_id":"SV-281053","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400180","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce group ownership by \"root\" or a restricted logging group for audit log files to prevent unauthorized access.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 to enforce group ownership by \"root\" or a restricted logging group for audit log files to prevent unauthorized access.\n\nIdentify the group that is configured to own the audit log:\n\n$ sudo grep -P '^[ ]*log_group[ ]+=.*$' /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nChange the ownership to that group using the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp ${log_group} ${log_file}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 enforces group ownership by \"root\" or a restricted logging group for audit log files to prevent unauthorized access.\n\nDetermine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep \"^log_file\" /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nDetermine the audit log group by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep -P '^[ ]*log_group[ ]+=.*$' /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_group = root\n\nCheck that the audit log file is owned by the correct group. Run the following command to display the owner of the audit log file:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%n %G\" /var/log/audit/audit.log\n/var/log/audit/audit.log root\n\nThe audit log file must be owned by the \"log_group\" or by \"root\" if the \"log_group\" is not specified.\n\nIf audit log files are owned by the incorrect group, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized disclosure of audit records can reveal system and configuration data to attackers, thus compromising its confidentiality.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"7981","uuid":"ac5991d9-146e-4a1e-b6f9-52e485eb93ca","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-281054","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281054","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281054","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-281054r1197224_rule","rule_id":"SV-281054","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400185","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must set mode \"0600\" or less permissive for the audit logs file to prevent unauthorized access to the audit log.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 audit logs to have a mode of \"0600\" with the following command:\n\nReplace \"[audit_log_file]\" with the path to each audit log file. By default, these logs are located in \"/var/log/audit/\":\n\n$ sudo chmod 0600 /var/log/audit/[audit_log_file]\n\nCheck the group that owns the system audit logs:\n\n$ sudo grep -iw log_group /etc/audit/auditd.conf\n\nIf \"log_group\" is set to a user other than \"root\", configure the permissions the following way:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0640 $log_file\n$ sudo chmod 0440 $log_file.*\n\nOtherwise, configure the permissions the following way:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0600 $log_file\n$ sudo chmod 0400 $log_file.*","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 audit logs have a mode of \"0600\".\n\nDetermine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep \"^log_file\" /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nUsing the location of the audit log file, determine the mode of each audit log with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find /var/log/audit/ -type f -exec stat -c '%a %n' {} \\;\n600 /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nIf the audit logs have a mode more permissive than \"0600\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify the RHEL 10 system or platform. Additionally, personally identifiable information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"9557","uuid":"d79325cb-e750-4134-a31c-76f28093ea05","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 28A240BA86CD0C829F3456E893761F5BE299AE80\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must set mode \"0600\" or less permissive for the audit logs file to prevent unauthorized access to the audit log.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281055","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281055","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281055","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-281055r1165520_rule","rule_id":"SV-281055","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400190","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce the audit log directory to have a mode of \"0750\" or less permissive to prevent unauthorized read access.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the audit log directories have a mode of \"0750\" or less permissive to prevent unauthorized read access with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0700 /var/log/audit\n\nNote: The correct permissions are \"0700\" if the directory is owned by \"root\"; otherwise, the correct permissions are \"0750\".\n\nRestart the audit daemon with the following command for the changes to take effect:\n\n$ sudo service auditd restart","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 enforces the audit log directory to have a mode of \"0750\" or less permissive to prevent unauthorized read access.\n\nDetermine where the audit logs are stored with the following command:\n\n$ sudo grep \"^log_file\" /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_file = /var/log/audit/audit.log\n\nFind the group that owns audit logs:\n\n$ sudo grep \"^log_group\" /etc/audit/auditd.conf\nlog_group = root\n\nRun the following command to check the mode of the system audit logs:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%a %n\" [audit_log_directory]\n\nReplace \"[audit_log_directory]\" to the correct audit log directory path; by default this location is \"/var/log/audit\".\n\nIf the log_group is \"root\" or is not set, the correct permissions are \"0700\".\n \nIf the log_group is owned by anyone other than \"root\", the correct permissions are \"0750\".\n\nIf audit logs have a more permissive mode than is required, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If users can write to audit logs, audit trails can be modified or destroyed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"2578","uuid":"ca0fcb24-1925-47f5-b165-b2874483e06c","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A0B6E6AE82F70BCB8821668A4B63903ADADBE3C3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce the audit log directory to have a mode of \"0750\" or less permissive to prevent unauthorized read access.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281056","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281056","title":"SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281056","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","rule_id_src":"SV-281056r1165523_rule","rule_id":"SV-281056","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400195","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce root ownership of the \"/etc/audit/\" directory.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the \"/etc/audit/\" directory is owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chown root /etc/audit/","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 enforces root ownership of the \"/etc/audit/\" directory with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%U %n\" /etc/audit/\nroot /etc/audit/\n\nIf the \"/etc/audit/\" directory does not have an owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/etc/audit/\" directory contains files that ensure the proper auditing of command execution, privilege escalation, file manipulation, and more. Protection of this directory is critical for system security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000171"],"reference_identifier":"6216","uuid":"6d5e21a7-cf13-405e-80dc-262b387055f6","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D32D35B15C19A93F7348F4CBE4091C6F21BFC5C\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'RHEL 10 must enforce root ownership of the \"/etc/audit/\" directory.' is not present or not in use on this the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281057","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281057","title":"SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281057","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","rule_id_src":"SV-281057r1165526_rule","rule_id":"SV-281057","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400200","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce root group ownership of the \"/etc/audit/\" directory.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the \"/etc/audit/\" directory is group-owned by \"root\" with the following command:\n\n$ sudo chgrp root /etc/audit/","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 enforces root group ownership of the \"/etc/audit/\" directory with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%G %n\" /etc/audit/\nroot /etc/audit/\n\nIf \"/etc/audit/\" does not have a group owner of \"root\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/etc/audit/\" directory contains files that ensure the proper auditing of command execution, privilege escalation, file manipulation, and more. Protection of this directory is critical for system security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000171"],"reference_identifier":"5177","uuid":"0e6d7dbb-184f-485c-974b-2a43ab060bc7","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 007FFA34FFF8FDDC3778319CDE23AB6F50B6A7DA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce root group ownership of the \"/etc/audit/\" directory.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281058","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281058","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281058","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281058r1165529_rule","rule_id":"SV-281058","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400205","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"755\" or less permissive for system commands.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the system commands to be protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[FILE]\" with any system command with a mode more permissive than \"755\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 755 [FILE]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the system commands contained in the following directories have mode \"755\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /bin /sbin /usr/bin /usr/sbin /usr/libexec /usr/local/bin /usr/local/sbin -perm /022 -exec ls -l {} \\;\n\nIf any system commands are found to be group-writable or world-writable, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"5458","uuid":"831f13ea-aa83-4179-a692-10156f8cb1a8","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F1EE55984A30A1F9FDE507B38C8478BB9A8F4973\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"755\" or less permissive for system commands.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281059","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281059","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281059","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281059r1165532_rule","rule_id":"SV-281059","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400210","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"755\" or less permissive on library directories.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the systemwide shared library directories (/lib, /lib64, /usr/lib, and /usr/lib64) are protected from unauthorized access.\n\nRun the following command, replacing \"[DIRECTORY]\" with any library directory with a mode more permissive than \"755\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 755 [DIRECTORY]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the systemwide shared library directories have mode \"755\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -perm /022 -type d -exec ls -l {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library file is found to be group-writable or world-writable, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"9502","uuid":"8483e140-2ddd-4d60-8dfd-5b2a963225fc","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1F4A704FD827793D1AF822D5AFDC5E4B1E2F41F2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"755\" or less permissive on library directories.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281060","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281060","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281060","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-281060r1165535_rule","rule_id":"SV-281060","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400215","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"755\" or less permissive for library files.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the library files are protected from unauthorized access. Run the following command, replacing \"[FILE]\" with any library file with a mode more permissive than \"755\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 755 [FILE]","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the systemwide shared library files contained in the following directories have mode \"755\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo find -L /lib /lib64 /usr/lib /usr/lib64 -perm /022 -type f -exec ls -l {} \\;\n\nIf any systemwide shared library file is found to be group-writable or world-writable, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If RHEL 10 allowed any user to make changes to software libraries, those changes might be implemented without undergoing the appropriate testing and approvals that are part of a robust change management process.\n\nThis requirement applies to RHEL 10 with software libraries that are accessible and configurable, as in the case of interpreted languages. Software libraries also include privileged programs that execute with escalated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"2941","uuid":"70ead0b6-3c65-4097-8393-d93acdca97b9","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 56715A39F81F6A9E4456CCC4E1E2C9B4592EFB16\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"755\" or less permissive for library files.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281061","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281061","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281061","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-281061r1165538_rule","rule_id":"SV-281061","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400220","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0755\" or less permissive for the \"/var/log\" directory.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the \"/var/log\" directory has a mode of \"0755\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0755 /var/log","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the \"/var/log\" directory has a mode of \"0755\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c '%a %n' /var/log\n755 /var/log\n\nIf \"/var/log\" does not have a mode of \"0755\" or less permissive, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify the RHEL 10 system or platform. Additionally, personally identifiable information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"7255","uuid":"ea182b0a-1dfd-4621-9621-ade7d7b14436","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 01C82EF76A179A5118412FF8C74DA9C178365DAD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0755\" or less permissive for the \"/var/log\" directory.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281062","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281062","title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281062","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","rule_id_src":"SV-281062r1165541_rule","rule_id":"SV-281062","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400225","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0640\" or less permissive for the \"/var/log/messages\" file.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the \"/var/log/messages\" file has a mode of \"0640\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0640 /var/log/messages","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the \"/var/log/messages\" file has a mode of \"0640\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ stat -c '%a %n' /var/log/messages\n600 /var/log/messages\n\nIf \"/var/log/messages\" does not have a mode of \"0640\" or less permissive, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Only authorized personnel should be aware of errors and the details of the errors. Error messages are an indicator of an organization's operational state or can identify the RHEL 10 system or platform. Additionally, personally identifiable information (PII) and operational information must not be revealed through error messages to unauthorized personnel or their designated representatives.\n\nThe structure and content of error messages must be carefully considered by the organization and development team. The extent to which the information system is able to identify and handle error conditions is guided by organizational policy and operational requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314"],"reference_identifier":"4972","uuid":"e0bbad89-660f-4d51-a3f2-763545b1b7fc","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-281063","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281063","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281063","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-281063r1195403_rule","rule_id":"SV-281063","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400230","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must be configured to prohibit modification of permissions for cron configuration files and directories from the operating system defaults.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 to prohibit modification of permissions for cron configuration files and directories from the operating system defaults with the following commands:\n\n$ sudo dnf reinstall cronie crontabs\n$ rpm --setugids cronie crontabs\n$ rpm --setperms cronie crontabs","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the owner, group, and mode of cron configuration files and directories match the operating system defaults with the following command:\n\n$ rpm --verify cronie crontabs | awk '! ($2 == \"c\" && $1 ~ /^.\\..\\.\\.\\.\\..\\./) {print $0}'\n\nIf the command returns any output, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the permissions of cron configuration files or directories are modified from the operating system defaults, it may be possible for individuals to insert unauthorized cron jobs that perform unauthorized actions, including potentially escalating privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7272","uuid":"845563e0-849a-4af4-a7d7-65e115e84072","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CD99615AF824E7ADEE4548D4A97E888C7A58D718\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must be configured to prohibit modification of permissions for cron configuration files and directories from the operating system defaults.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281064","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281064","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281064","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281064r1165547_rule","rule_id":"SV-281064","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400235","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0740\" or less permissive for local initialization files.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that all local initialization files have a mode of \"0740\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\nNote: The example will be for the \"disauser\" user, who has a home directory of \"/home/disauser\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 0740 /home/disauser/.<INIT_FILE>","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that all local initialization files have a mode of \"0740\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\nNote: The example will be for the \"disauser\" user, who has a home directory of \"/home/disauser\".\n\n$ sudo find /home -maxdepth 2 -type f -name \".*\" -exec stat -c \"%n %a\" {} \\; | awk '$2 > 740'\n/home/disauser/.bash_profile 770 \n\nIf any local initialization files are returned, this indicates a mode more permissive than \"0740\", and this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Local initialization files are used to configure the user's shell environment upon login. Malicious modification of these files could compromise accounts upon login.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"4386","uuid":"3fcd99b1-2ec2-4729-943f-30c648958fba","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B8B96D845F79B240E401254D315563B054DFFC9B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0740\" or less permissive for local initialization files.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281065","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281065","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281065","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281065r1165550_rule","rule_id":"SV-281065","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400240","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0750\" or less permissive for local interactive user home directories.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the mode of interactive user's home directories is set to \"0750\". \n\nTo change the mode of a local interactive user's home directory, use the following command:\n\nNote: The example will be for the user \"disauser\".\n\n$ sudo chmod 0750 /home/disauser","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the assigned home directory of all local interactive users has a mode of \"0750\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\nNote: This may miss interactive users that have been assigned a privileged user identifier (UID). Evidence of interactive use may be obtained from a number of log files containing system login information.\n\n$ stat -L -c '%a %n' $(awk -F: '($3>=1000)&&($7 !~ /nologin/){print $6}' /etc/passwd) 2>/dev/null\n700 /home/disauser\n\nIf home directories referenced in \"/etc/passwd\" do not have a mode of \"0750\" or less permissive, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Excessive permissions on local interactive user home directories may allow unauthorized access to user files by other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"3905","uuid":"c8e1470b-ccec-4b44-b505-6ebef33260aa","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b115-428d-9158-12d640fd1211","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL10_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 80CB35D883B552A6483DD975C0A21A28FF0C3D5A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0750\" or less permissive for local interactive user home directories.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 10 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-281066","group_tree":[{"id":"V-281066","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-281066","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-281066r1165553_rule","rule_id":"SV-281066","rule_version":"RHEL-10-400245","rule_title":"RHEL 10 must enforce mode \"0644\" or less permissive for the \"/etc/group\" file to prevent unauthorized access.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 10 so that the mode of the file \"/etc/group\" is set to \"0644\" by running the following command:\n\n$ sudo chmod 0644 /etc/group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify RHEL 10 is configured so that the \"/etc/group\" file has mode \"0644\" or less permissive with the following command:\n\n$ sudo stat -c \"%a %n\" /etc/group\n644 /etc/group\n\nIf a value of \"0644\" or less permissive is not returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_10_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"/etc/group\" file contains information regarding groups that are configured on the system. Protection of this file is important for system security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"7523","uuid":"cedcab2a-e814-468e-9048-7fd4839be088","stig_uuid":"a68f390c-b1